RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISSIONARY pressured the pace through the backstretch, took the lead three wide at the quarter pole and was steadily handled in the lane. LASTWALKTOFREEDOM broke a step slow then gave chase, rounded the turn near the rail and finished evenly while clearing second in later yards. J. EVANESCO chased the early pace inside, was eased to the four path into the far turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. DR RENDEZVOUS was hustled to contention and took the edge nearing the three eighths pole, gave up the lead at the quarter and weakened. WINDSOR'S STAR was pulled up lame shortly after the start and was vanned off.

RAISE A SPEIGHTS rounded the opening turn in the four path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the six path on the far turn, bore wider into the lane but finished well to take second the final strides while gaining on the winner. SUPER QUALITY took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and angled to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane, but gave up the lead in the final yards. HAPPY CHARLIE settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase leaving the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and ran evenly in the lane. ROYAL THUNDER raced off the rail the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and ran evenly to mid-stretch before flattening stride. ROCKY DICE raced in the three path the first turn, left the turn outside and showed little response through the backstretch, rounded the far turn in the seven path and was carried wider into the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EMBERLY stalked from the three quarter pole, challenged approaching the three eighths and took over toward the five sixteenths, dueled clear at the rail midway on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on well. SKY BUY raced off the rail the opening turn, started a three wide bid leaving the three eighths pole, contested at a close disadvantage off the rail on the far turn and settled for second. WINDSOR'S PLAY came away awkwardly but took the lead leaving the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to show the way, came under pressure nearing the three eighths, was met toward the five sixteenths pole and flattened at the rail on the far turn. BREADMAN'S ROSEBUD raced in the three path the first turn, left the turn outside and gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the four and five paths and could only improve her position in the lane. BEST VIRGINIA raced two deep the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, drifted toward the head of the lane and flattened stride. HERETODAYGONMANANA saved ground and showed little response through the backstretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 29400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 25 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility) .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRY WELL saved ground off the early pace, eased out into the backstretch and started a bid toward the three eighths pole, dueled to even terms two deep approaching the head of the lane and dug in determinedly to edge clear of DULCIMER DAME in later yards. The latter saved ground close to the pace then eased out into the backstretch, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, dueled to a slim lead past the five sixteenths, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn but was met toward the head of the lane and reluctantly ceded. SIDESWIPED saved early ground racing well back, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and steadily improved, rounded the far turn about the seven path and finished well to take third mid-stretch. KALENJIN rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and flattened in the lane. LACE REVOLUTION saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path and weakened. BABA rated a slim lead inside, was met past the nine sixteenths pole but briefly recovered the edge approaching the three eighths, gave up the lead again at the five sixteenths and weakened at the rail on the far turn. SMOOCHINWITHCINDY came away awkwardly then stalked two deep, took the nod past the nine sixteenths pole but was met passing the half mile pole and gave way at the rail into the far turn. COMPLETE SURPRISE was shuffled back soon after the start then stalked from the three path the opening turn, took the lead three wide passing the half mile pole but was met toward the three eighths and faded past the five sixteenths.

ENTRY.NAME: Baba
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead,met past 9/16,caught 5/16,weakened rail far turn

Entries close Wednesday, November 22, 2023 by the usual time of closing. RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUBAWITHATWIST stalked from the three path the opening turn, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced close in the three path the far turn, drew to even terms into the lane, dueled clear mid-stretch and widened with steady handling. KING KONTIE took the lead and moved to the inside to show the way, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole and contested the advantage off the rail on the far turn, was met into the lane and dueled close through the upper stretch, but dropped back toward the sixteenth pole and settled for second best. MAKANI settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and showed little more. GOLD CREATIONS steadied soon after the start then saved ground and showed little response through the backstretch. CANDY FOR JUBA stalked from the four path the opening turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn.

ESTRELLA FUGAZ became anxious in the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn about the four path and weakened.
